## b. Type and coordinate estimation error:

According to Theorems 2.2, we decompose the score estimation error into two components: atom type estimation error and coordinate estimation error, which are compared experimentally. For atom type estimation, we compare the accumulated denoising loss $\sqrt{l \sum_{t=1}^{T} \mathcal{L}_{t}^{(h \mid x)}}$ and prediction loss $\frac{1}{2} \mathbb{E}_{q\left(\boldsymbol{x}_{0}\right)} \mathcal{L}^{(h)}\left(\boldsymbol{x}_{0}\right)$. For coordinate estimation, we evaluate the results of two denoising losses $\sqrt{l \sum_{t=1}^{T} \mathcal{L}_{t}^{(x \mid h)}}$ and $\sqrt{l \sum_{t=1}^{T} \mathcal{L}_{t}^{(x)}}$. It is important to note that the input of the network differs in the two denoising losses, with $\mathcal{L}_{t}^{(x \mid h)}$ incorporating noisy atom type as input:

$$
\begin{aligned}
\mathcal{L}_{t}^{(x \mid h)} & =\mathbb{E}_{q\left(\boldsymbol{z}_{0}, \boldsymbol{z}_{n}\right)}\left(\left\|\boldsymbol{\phi}_{\theta}^{(x)}\left(\boldsymbol{z}_{t}, t\right)-\left(-\sigma_{t} \nabla_{\boldsymbol{x}_{t}} \log q\left(\boldsymbol{x}_{t}\right)\right)\right\|^{2} \\
\mathcal{L}_{t}^{(x)} & =\mathbb{E}_{q\left(\boldsymbol{x}_{0}, \boldsymbol{x}_{n}\right)}\left(\left\|\boldsymbol{\phi}_{\theta}^{(x)}\left(\boldsymbol{x}_{t}, t\right)-\left(-\sigma_{t} \nabla_{\boldsymbol{x}_{t}} \log q\left(\boldsymbol{x}_{t}\right)\right)\right\|^{2}
\end{aligned}
$$

The detailed experimental comparison and analysis is presented in Section 2.2, showing UniGem achieves lower atom types and coordinates estimation error.
